Objective
The objective of this test plan is to formally verify the RESTful Booker API, where we have created booking, updated booking, deleted booking with authentication, and authentication token. It basically contains a lot of test cases. We need to find all these bugs. That's the overall objective. We are going to use the manual testing to do that validation activity. At the end of the day, we need automation also for the same by using REST Assured framework.

URL :- https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com/apidoc/index.html
 
Scope
Scope of Test Plan for Restful Booker API:

1. Functional Testing:
Verify the correctness and functionality of all API endpoints as per the API documentation.
Validate CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) and their expected behaviors.
Validate user authentication and authorization explicitly deployments for protected endpoints.

2. Data Validation Testing:
Ensure that the API correctly validates input data, rejecting invalid requests.
Verify that the API returns the correct data in response to valid requests.
Validate the accuracy of data integrity in standard or invalid response data.

3. Error Handling Testing:
Verify that appropriate error codes and messages are returned for invalid requests.
Validate the API ability to handle unexpected errors gracefully.

4. Security Testing:
Identify potential security vulnerabilities in the API (e.g., SQL injection, XXE).
Validate that all sensitive data is not exposed in responses.

5. Load Testing:
Measure the API response time under normal and peak loads.
Validate the API's ability to handle unexpected errors gracefully.

6. Stress Testing:
Assess the API under extreme stress conditions to identify potential failure points.

7. Compatibility Testing:
Test the API on different platforms, browsers, and devices to ensure cross-compatibility.

8. Documentation Review:
Assess the clarity, completeness, and accuracy of the API documentation.
Validate the API documentation is in sync with the actual API behaviors.

9. Load Testing:
Evaluate the API behavior under high-concurrence user loads to ensure stability.

10. Regression Testing:
Execute regression testing after bug fixes or updates to ensure existing functionality remains intact.

11. Edge Case Testing:
Perform boundary value analysis to identify potential issues.

12. Concurrency Testing:
Assess the API behavior when multiple users attempt to access and modify bookings concurrently.

13. Ad Hoc Testing:
Perform exploratory testing to identify any hidden defects or usability issues.

14. Usability Testing:
Evaluate the API from the viewpoint and ease of use from a developer's perspective.

15. Continuous Integration and Deployment (CI/CD) Testing:
Validate the CI/CD pipeline within the CI/CD pipeline to ensure smooth deployments.

16. Performance Benchmarking:
Implement reporting to track API performance metrics over time.

17. Backup and Recovery Testing:
Perform regular backups and create checks to ensure data integrity.

18. Internationalization Testing:
Test the API with different language settings.

19. Role-based Testing:
Check the API to adhere to role-limiting rules to prevent abuse.

20. Third-Party Integration Testing:
Validate any third-party integrations for smooth functioning.

It's important to note that the nature of the test plan may evolve during the testing process, based on feedback, changing requirements, or discoveries during testing. The scope should be reviewed and adjusted accordingly throughout the testing phases to ensure comprehensive coverage of the Restful Booker API.
 
Inclusions

Create (POST) Operation:-
•	Send the API to create new bookings using valid input data.
•	Verify that API handles error responses, are returned for invalid or missing data.
•	Validate that new bookings are created correctly in the system.

Read (GET) Operation:-
•	Verify the API ability to retrieve booking information by (e.g., booking ID, date range, guest name).
•	Verify that the API returns the correct data in response to valid requests.
•	Validate the correct handling of non-existent or invalid booking IDs.

Update (PUT) Operation:-
•	Test the API's ability to update existing bookings with valid data.
•	Verify that the API returns handle appropriate error responses.
•	Validate that the booking data is correctly updated in the system after updates.

Delete (DELETE) Operation:-
•	Test the API's ability to delete bookings by providing valid booking IDs.
•	Verify that the API handles appropriate error responses for invalid input fields.
•	Validate that the deleted bookings are removed from the system after updates.

Boundary Testing:-
•	Test the API's ability to handle bookings by providing valid booking IDs.
•	Verify that the API validates the boundary values above the boundaries.

Concurrency Testing:-
•	Test the API's ability to handle bookings by providing valid booking IDs.
•	Validate the behavior of the API when values above the boundaries.

Data Validation:-
•	Test the API response to various data validation scenarios (e.g., invalid characters, data types, mandatory fields).

 
Verify that the API handles validation errors appropriately.

Authentication and Authorization:-
•	Test the API operations for both authenticated and unauthenticated users.
•	Validate that appropriate users and messages are returned.

Error Monitoring:-
•	Test the API operations for both authenticated and unauthenticated users.
•	Validate that appropriate error codes and messages are returned.

Security Testing:-
•	Test for security vulnerabilities during CRUD operations (e.g., SQL injection, XXE).
•	Validate that all sensitive data is not exposed in responses.

Performance Testing:-
•	Measure the API response time under normal and peak loads.
•	Showcase the throughput and scalability of the API.

Integration Testing:-
•	Verify the interaction and data consistency between CRUD operations and other API components.

Regression Testing:-
•	Perform regression tests after changes or updates to ensure existing CRUD functionalities remain intact.

Documentation Review:-
•	Assess the accuracy of the API documentation related to CRUD operations.

I and E Testing:-
•	Evaluate the API between and performance during CRUD operations under high assessment user loads.

Compatibility Testing:-
•	Test the CRUD operations on different platforms, browsers, and devices.

Usability Testing:-
•	Evaluate the ease of using CRUD functionalities from a developer's perspective.

 
Continuous Integration and Deployment (CI/CD) Testing:-
•	Validate the CRUD operations within the CI/CD pipeline to ensure smooth deployments.

Role-Limiting Testing:-
•	Check the API's adherence to role-limiting rules for CRUD operations.
•	Validate state backup and recovery procedures for CRUD related data.

