Defect Reporting Procedure

This outlines for identifying a defect, such as a deviation from the requirements, save opportunities issues, or functional deviations.

The steps for reporting a defect, such as using a designated template, providing detailed information about the issue, and including screenshots or logs.

The process for triaging and prioritizing defects, such as assigning severity and priority levels, and assigning them to the appropriate team members for investigation and resolution.

The tools and systems that will be used to measure the effectiveness of the defect reporting process, track on them, get updates and for managing defects, such as a defect tracking software or a project management tool.

 
The roles and responsibilities of the team members involved in the defect reporting process, such as testers, developers, and the test lead.

The communication channels and frequencies for updating relevant stakeholders on the progress and status of defects.

