Test Strategy

The first step is to create test scenarios and test cases for the various features in the Booker Application.

While developing test cases, we will follow a number of test design techniques:
•	Equivalence Value Analysis
•	Boundary Value Analysis
•	Decision Table Testing
•	State Transition Testing
•	Use Case Testing

We will also take into consideration in writing Test Cases by applying the below:
•	Error Guessing
•	Exploratory Testing
•	We will prioritize the Test Cases.

Step 2: Our testing procedure when we receive a request for testing:
•	First, well-considered individual testing to test for various and test
 
important functionalities of the application are working.

•	We report the finds in bug-tracking tools and will work for the Booker Testing role in the stable editor performing or simply testing the application functionalities.

•	Once we receive a stable build which passes Smoke Testing, we perform or start testing using the following plan for the stable builds:

•	Multiple Test Resources will be testing the same Application on Multiple Requested Environment simultaneously.

Step 3: We will follow the below best practices to make our testing better:
•	Contract Driven Testing: We will be performing Testing as per the context of the given application.
•	Shift Left Testing: We will start testing from the beginning stages of the development build instead of testing for stable builds.
•	Exploratory Testing: Using our expertise we will perform Exploratory testing paper from the initial iteration of the first sprint.
•	End to End Post Plan Testing: We will test the end to end scenario which enables multiple modules running functionality to end user flows.

